Indurain Wins Alentejo Cycling Race 
Miguel Indurain of Spain won the Alentejo cycling tour here on
Saturday, beating his younger brother Prudencio by 26 seconds in the
final standings.
The five-time winner of the Tour de France only managed 21st in the
eighth and final 184km stage between Borba and Evora, but neverthleless
kept the yellow jersey from the beginning to the end of the event.
His Compatriot Asier Guenetxea sprinted home to win Saturdays stage in
four hours 47 minutes seven seconds.
